    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of Eurasian tree around 30 m (100 feet) in height and having a grayish-white trunk and wavy-margined, wedge-shaped leaves up to 15 cm (6 inches) in length. It is sometimes classified as a subspecies of Fagus sylvatica, to which it is closely related.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
